  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering through several key mechanisms:\n\n1. International Conventions and Treaties\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Establish common standards and obligations\n\n2. Legal Cooperation Mechanisms\n- Mutual Legal Assistance Treaties (MLATs)\n- Extradition agreements\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Joint investigative efforts\n\n3. Regulatory Compliance Standards\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting\n- Customer due diligence protocols\n- Uniform international reporting standards\n\n4. Enforcement Coordination\n- Interpol financial crime networks\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Shared intelligence platforms\n- Harmonized legal definitions\n\n5. Sanctions and Penalties\n- International blacklisting of non-compliant jurisdictions\n- Economic sanctions\n- Coordinated financial restrictions\n- International asset freezing mechanisms\n\n6. Technological Collaboration\n- Cross-border digital financial tracking\n- Blockchain transparency initiatives\n- Advanced forensic financial analysis tools\n\nThese intersections create a comprehensive global framework for preventing, detecting, and prosecuting money laundering activities across different legal jurisdictions.",
